  <main>
    <h2 style="font-size: 35px; text-align: center; color: #00a7cc ">Water Parameters</h2>
    <section>
      <h3>EC</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 0.3 mS/cm</li>
        <li>Maximum: 3.0 mS/cm</li>
        <li>Note: Indicates the water’s ability to conduct electricity, affecting plant growth.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>SG</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 1.000</li>
        <li>Maximum: 1.200</li>
        <li>Note: Reflects density and potential for concentration issues.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>Salinity</h3>
      <ul>
      <li>Minimum: 0.1 g/L</li>
      <li>Maximum: 10.0 g/L (parts per thousand)</li>
      <li>Note:  Affects plant water uptake and soil salinity.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>ORP</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: -100 mV</li>
        <li>Maximum: 800 mV</li>
        <li>Note: Measures water’s oxidation-reduction potential, affecting nutrient availability.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>TDS</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 200 mg/L (ppm)</li>
        <li>Maximum: 2000 mg/L (ppm)</li>
        <li>Note: Affects soil health and nutrient availability.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>pH</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 6.0</li>
        <li>Maximum: 8.5</li>
        <li>Note:  Impacts nutrient availability and soil pH balance.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Temperature</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 5°C</li>
        <li>Maximum: 40°C</li>
        <li>Note:  Influences the water’s impact on plant roots and soil conditions.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
